d keep a file called reflect-config.json in the META-INF/native-image directory. I need to clarify that this part is essential for proper configuration and functionality. Let’s ensure that I address this properly!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating metadata conditions**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking that adding test-specific metadata might not be necessary. If the condition isn't satisfied, I should indeed fail. I need to check the native image metadata format in the H2 source, which uses `\\\\\\\"typeReachable\\\\\\\"` while repository metadata uses `\\\\\\\"typeReached\\\\\\\"`. If the Native Image version supports `\\\\\\\"typeReachable\\\\\\\"`, that could be possible. However, older documentation refers to `\\\\\\\"typeReachable\\\\\\\"`, and I might need to test the H2 jar to ensure everything works. The official repository's metadata is crucial!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing repository and tests**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering that the repository might be intentionally just extra, so I shouldn’t add duplicate official items. I need to ensure dynamic access coverage counts. If my test class calls `TraceSystem.setLevelFile`, reaching line 197 doesn't necessarily mean success. I think it may still record attempted calls, even if reflection metadata is missing. Using an SLF4J dependency in H2 tests seems necessary for active classes. I also need to ensure the order of class variables and consider using `testImplementation` instead of `testRuntimeOnly`. Before committing, I'll check the git diff.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_gtQ2R3g3WrYhDLusKOvm9Nz6|fc_0e7839a16ff5c7a80169f1162c8e7881a29288e284bf29d78c\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git add tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/build.gradle tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/java/h2/TraceSystemTest.java && git commit -m \\\"Add H2 TraceSystem adapter coverage\\\"\", \"timeout\": 30}}], \"api\": \"opena