imitations with static finals, reflecting on whether I can modify things through an alternative fork. The public API doesn’t allow for that. I’m wondering if I could run a dedicated test that uses a property only. But it seems like Gradle’s per-test system property just can’t work since it applies to everything. Maybe I can take a look at JdbcUtilsTest’s default method to see if it can set the appropriate context?\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating serialization options**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether to keep the active configuration in a dedicated way by changing the default `defaultSerializationRoundTripStillUsesJdbcUtils`. Should I provide an explicit `JavaObjectSerializer` set to null? Actually, there's a possibility that I could just remove it since default deserialization is already covered. However, changing this might affect existing tests, which could still call `JdbcUtils.deserialize` with the null serializer. I think I need to search for more details to clear this up!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_LCpgxqOez62I2BpdpqMgwD5g|fc_071ac4cc282b3ce10169f11394a03481949d1c41634a260ade\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg -n \\\"JdbcUtils\\\\.deserialize|USE_THREAD_CONTEXT_CLASS_LOADER|useThreadContext\\\" tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/java tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/resources tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/build.gradle\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 655, \"output\": 1200, \"cacheRead\": 23552, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 25407, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777406847917, \"responseId\": \"resp_071ac4cc282b3ce10169f113806e048194a219e1a3ae323b99\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_LCpgxqOez62I2BpdpqMgwD5g|fc_071