\\\\\\"\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void scalesValueForAvailableMemory() {\\n        assertThat(Utils.scaleForAvailableMemory(1)).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(0);\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class UtilityFixture {\\n        private final String name;\\n        private final int count;\\n\\n        public UtilityFixture() {\\n            this(\\\"default\\\", 0);\\n        }\\n\\n        public UtilityFixture(String name, int count) {\\n            this.name = name;\\n            this.count = count;\\n        }\\n\\n        public static String join(String left, String right) {\\n            return left + ':' + right;\\n        }\\n\\n        public String describe(String prefix) {\\n            return prefix + ':' + name + ':' + count;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public String toString() {\\n            return name + ':' + count;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1801, \"output\": 1088, \"cacheRead\": 35328, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 38217, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777402229595, \"responseId\": \"resp_01ec786bdc7a64a00169f101766d4081a1b08705cafa4b9245\"}}\n4035:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating reflection needs**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need to add `com.sun.management.OperatingSystemMXBean` for native reflection. The method `getTotalPhysicalMemorySize` isn't registered in the native image, so maybe I should add it to reflect-config. It appears the native image may not automatically include JDK reflection, so I'm adding the necessary metadata. I’m also pondering if I need to handle the `org.h2.util.Utils` methods for static calls. Finally, I need to ensure I'm managing package visibility and imports properly while wri